German Interior Minister Hans-Peter Friedrich told Zeit Online: 'If Mr Snowden is willing to talk to German representatives, then we will find ways to make that possible.'
Relations between the US and Germany have been strained by allegations that the NSA tapped Chancellor Angela Merkel's mobile phone.
Thomas Oppermann, the lawmaker who chairs the House Intelligence Committee, said that the opportunity should be taken to hear Snowden as a witness, if possible, "without jeopardizing him and completely ruining relations with the US."
Ströbele, a Green MP, posted a picture of himself and Snowden on his Twitter feed.
